    "body": "This fixes the selection between grouped vs per-tensor or per-token quantization. In some cases, the linear layers will pass in transposed scales (e.g. 1 x num_tokens instead of num_tokens x 1). This simplifies and makes the dispatching to the per-token/per-channel/per-tensor case more flexible.\n\nFixes the error:\n```\nE       RuntimeError: Unsupported scale group shapes for CUTLASS 3.x GEMM.\nE        a_scale_group_shape must be [1, 128], got: [1, 2048]\nE       b_scale_group_shape must be [128, 128], got: [1, 2560]\n```\nwhen running for example: `vllm serve nm-testing/TinyLlama-1.1B-Chat-v1.0-FP8_DYNAMIC-e2e`\n",
    "created_at": "2025-02-03T15:54:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-02-03T21:05:00Z",
